        "name": "Johannes Scheuermann",
        "username": "johscheuer",
        "avatar_template": "https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/j/f475e1/{size}.png",
        "created_at": "2025-03-07T16:31:31.969Z",
        "cooked": "<p>You were on the right track with adding an additional container with the ProcessSettings, we actually have an example in our docs: <a href=\"https://github.com/FoundationDB/fdb-kubernetes-operator/blob/main/docs/manual/customization.md#customizing-your-pods\" class=\"inline-onebox\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">fdb-kubernetes-operator/docs/manual/customization.md at main \u00b7 FoundationDB/fdb-kubernetes-operator \u00b7 GitHub</a>. The statement</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If a container image with a tag is specified the operator will throw an error and stop processing the cluster.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Was referring to the main container and sidecar container as those versions (tags) are managed by the operator. We should adjust the wording here. Could you open a GitHub issue to improve the wording here (and if you want you can also file a PR, happy to review it).</p>",
